    <dashboard name='Story 2' type='storyboard'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontsize='15'>Slide 2</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='201' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size maxheight='664' maxwidth='1150' minheight='664' minwidth='1150' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='97590' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98608' x='696' y='1205'>
            <zone fixed-size='108' h='16265' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98608' x='696' y='1205' />
            <zone h='81325' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98608' x='696' y='17470'>
              <flipboard active-id='7' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='&quot;Year - On - Year Sales Trend&quot;' captured-sheet='Year-On-Year Sales' id='4' />
                  <story-point caption='&quot;Townwise Sales Ratio&quot;' captured-sheet='T5 Town - Sales Ratio' id='5' />
                  <story-point caption='&quot;Number of Properties with Sales Ratio&quot;' captured-sheet='Distribution of Property Types' id='6' />
                  <story-point caption='Key Insights:&#10;&#10;Recommendations:' captured-sheet='' id='7' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='24849' id='6' story-point-id='7' type-v2='text' w='88609' x='5565' y='20030'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Cambria' fontsize='13' underline='true'>Key Insights</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Cambria' fontsize='13'>- Transaction value grew ~14x from 2011 ($2.6B) to peak 2021 ($40B) </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Cambria' fontsize='13'>- Single Family dominates volume (52%, 273K properties) but Commercial properties show the highest Sales Ratio anomaly (11.69 avg) </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Cambria' fontsize='13'>- Town-level Sales Ratio reveals data quality outliers (Bellingham, Keene) that warrant investigation </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Cambria' fontsize='13'>- Total market value across dataset: $234.6B in sales, $169.4B in assessed value — a $65B gap (avg ratio 2.638)</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='18825' hidden='true' id='7' story-point-id='4' type-v2='text' w='48261' x='3913' y='18373'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Cambria'>Real estate transaction value grew nearly 14x between 2011 and 2021 — from $2.6B to a peak of $40B — before settling at $22B in 2022. This surge aligns with broader US housing market trends, including pandemic-era demand (2020-2021) and historically low interest rates during that period.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='21988' hidden='true' id='8' story-point-id='5' type-v2='text' w='49043' x='45130' y='34940'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Cambria'>&quot;While most towns show a healthy Sales Ratio between 1–3, a handful of outliers — including Bellingham (25.8) and Keene (14.9) — show extreme deviations. This likely points to inconsistent assessment practices or data entry errors in those specific town records, worth flagging for data quality review.&quot;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='55572' hidden='true' id='9' story-point-id='6' type-v2='text' w='22435' x='73826' y='27259'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Cambria'>&quot;Single Family homes dominate the market at 273K properties (52% of total), followed by Residential (112K) and Condo (69K) types. Notably, Commercial properties — while just 4K in volume — carry the highest average Sales Ratio at 11.69, suggesting commercial assessments lag significantly behind actual market sale prices compared to residential categories.&quot;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='27108' id='10' story-point-id='7' type-v2='text' w='81217' x='9826' y='56928'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Cambria' fontsize='13' underline='true'>Recommendations</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Cambria' fontsize='13'>- Audit assessment methodology for Commercial properties and outlier towns</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Cambria' fontsize='13'>- Treat pre-2011 records (10 rows) as data artifacts — exclude from trend analysis</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Cambria' fontsize='13'>- Use Sales Ratio as a flag for re-assessment prioritization, not just a reporting metric</run>
          </formatted-text>
